{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"48a4fcab-8e20-4cb5-96db-c0a2cce57ed5","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n- **Watch** for file changes and re-run automatically on save\n- **Filter** to only the `ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException` test\n\nOther filter options:\n\n```bash\n# By test name (shorter)\ndotnet watch test --filter \"Name=ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n\n# By class + test\ndotnet watch test --filter \"ClassName~PaymentTests&Name~NegativeAmount\"\n```\n\nRun this from your test project directory (where the `.csproj` is).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e072d613-b09c-44ae-8966-99c6798f8bbd","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to filter to a specific test while using hot reload, likely in a .NET context (given the test name style). Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":238,"requestId":"1BDD:37D8BB:242D295:280BC50:6A03DD4A"},"id":"301e4352-ad4c-4860-aa00-1c0811cd9806","timestamp":"2026-05-13T02:09:22.342Z","parentId":"dec35dec-e83c-4bb4-9874-5247cf52acb1"}
